# Trimmed to a handful of checks -- TestRunner fires at most one event per
# full loop() call, and this sketch's loop() is just delay(1000), so each
# extra assertion costs a full additional ~1s iteration. All the output is
# setup()-only and already true from t=0, so keeping the count low is purely
# about staying well inside the timeout, not about ordering or correctness.
0.2, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "concat: Hello, VEMCODE!"
0.4, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "length(): 23"
0.6, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "toInt(): 42"
0.8, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "=== done ==="
